<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
  <!-- The above 3 meta tags *must* come first in the head; any other head content must come *after* these tags -->
  <title>Project Page</title>

  <!-- Bootstrap -->
  <link href="css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">

  <!-- HTML5 shim and Respond.js for IE8 support of HTML5 elements and media queries -->
  <!-- WARNING: Respond.js doesn't work if you view the page via file:// -->
  <!--[if lt IE 9]>
  <script src="https://oss.maxcdn.com/html5shiv/3.7.2/html5shiv.min.js"></script>
  <script src="https://oss.maxcdn.com/respond/1.4.2/respond.min.js"></script>
  <![endif]-->
</head>
<body>

<div class="jumbotron">
  <div class="container">
    <h1>Project Page</h1>

    <p>This generated page visualizes project data in various types of graphs.
      The goal is to display metrics over the evolution of the project</p>
  </div>
</div>


<div class="page-header">
  <div class="container">
    <h1>Graphs and Visualations</h1>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="row">
  <div class="col-sm-6 col-md-6">
    <div class="thumbnail">
      <img src="loc.png">

      <div class="caption">
        <h3>Lines of Code Graph</h3>

        <p>The graph has the number of lines of code on the vertical axis and
          the hash commit on the horizontal axis. It displays lines of code,
          lines of library code, total lines of production code which is the
          lines of code and the library lines of code, the number of specs lines
          of code and the number of lines of comments. </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="col-sm-6 col-md-6">
    <div class="thumbnail">
      <img src="spec_run_time.png">

      <div class="caption">
        <h3>Specs Runtime Graph</h3>

        <p>The graph has the time on the vertical axis and the hash commit on
          the horizontal axis. The graph display the total time it took to run
          the specs in each commit</p>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</div>

<div class="row">
  <div class="col-sm-6 col-md-6">
    <div class="thumbnail">
      <img src="spec_to_prod_ratio.png">

      <div class="caption">
        <h3>Specs to Production Lines of Code Ratio Graph</h3>

        <p>The graph has the ratio of spec lines of code to total production
          lines of code on the vertical axis and the hash commit on
          the horizontal axis.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="col-sm-6 col-md-6">
    <div class="thumbnail">
      <img src="coverage.png">

      <div class="caption">
        <h3>Code Coverage Graph</h3>

        <p>The graph displays number of lines of code on the vertical axis and
          the hash commit on
          the horizontal axis. The graph displays two lines. The first is the
          number of lines of code covered by the running specs. The second is
          the number of total lines of production code.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</div>

<div class="row">
  <div class="col-sm-6 col-md-6">
    <div class="thumbnail">
      <img src="coverage_ratio.png">

      <div class="caption">
        <h3>Coverage Ratio Graph</h3>

        <p>The graph has the ratio of production lines of code covered by the
          running specs to total production
          lines of code on the vertical axis and the hash commit on
          the horizontal axis.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>

  <div class="col-sm-6 col-md-6">
    <div class="thumbnail">
      <img src="number_of_files.png">

      <div class="caption">
        <h3>Number of Files Graph</h3>

        <p>Simple bar graph that displays the number of file per commit</p>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>

</div>

<div class="page-header">
  <div class="container">
    <h1>Project Data Table</h1>
  </div>
</div>

<table class="table table-striped">

  <tr>
    <th>
      Hash
    </th>
    <th>
      Commit Message
    </th>
    <th>
      Specs Runtime
    </th>
    <th>Application Lines</th>
    <th>Library Lines</th>
    <th>Spec Lines</th>
    <th>Comment Lines</th>
    <th>Number of Files</th>
    <th>Covered Lines</th>
    <th>Total Lines</th>
  </tr>

  <% @table.each do |row| %>
      <tr>
        <td>
          <%= row[0] %>
        </td>
        <td>
          <%= row[1] %>
        </td>
        <td>
          <%= row[2] %>
        </td>
        <td>
          <%= row[3] %>
        </td>
        <td>
          <%= row[4] %>
        </td>
        <td>
          <%= row[5] %>
        </td>
        <td>
          <%= row[6] %>
        </td>
        <td>
          <%= row[7] %>
        </td>
        <td>
          <%= row[8] %>
        </td>
        <td>
          <%= row[9] %>
        </td>
      </tr>
  <% end %>
</table>

<!-- jQuery (necessary for Bootstrap's JavaScript plugins) -->
<script src="https://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/1.11.3/jquery.min.js"></script>
<!-- Include all compiled plugins (below), or include individual files as needed -->
<script src="js/bootstrap.min.js"></script>
</body>
</html>